The 'Ohio Valley Conference' ('OVC') is a college athletic conference which
operates in the midwestern and southeastern United States. It participates in
Division I of the NCAA; the conference's football programs compete in the
Football Championship Subdivision (FCS; formerly known as Division I-AA), the
lower of two levels of Division I football competition. The OVC has 12 members,
9 of which compete in football in the conference.
